reviewText: This film is another of the charming summer weight stories from Sun Films.  A young journalism student is on her way to Alaska to do some filming as part of her masters thesis. Her adventure unfolds when she is stranded along the way due to aircraft problems.  She needs to share a room with another young woman also stranded by the disrupted flight.  This film is not on par with Albert Einstein running into Joe McCarthy,  (Insignificance, 1985) or earlier accidental roommate stories; nor will it satisfy someone expecting hard core bondage or "hot girl on girl action."  Though it does have bondage scenes, it's just a light hearted story closer to real people having real relationship experiences, as compared to romanticized theatre films or predictable pizza delivery guy classics.
This film is a pathetic waste of money. It provides nothing to the market for which it is advertised. It is completely boring and pointless.

One of the worst movies I have ever watched.  Two women end up having to share a hotel room when they are stranded ,due to airplane troubles.  One of the girls films everything and plans on using the footage as part of her thesis for school.  There is a scene where one girl gives the other girl a massage, there is a bathtub scene, and then there is a "bondage" scene, if you could even call it bondage.  There is no sex or romantic relationship at all, everything that happens is portrayed as platonic, which I feel makes the movie very unrealistic.  I can't say I have ever bathed any of my female friends in a platonic way.  There is not even any chemistry between the women.  The movie just has no point.
Charming story. Enjoyable to watch.

This is an indie film with fetish and erotic themes. Like almost all indie films it has it flaws. However, considering it is a first effort by a new studio, to my knowledge, its merits considerably out weigh its flaws. it is not a film to watch with your children unless they are very mature for their age. However, if you and your loved one are in the mood for an interesting work by a new studio I highly recommend Newsgirls.
More than what I thought it would be.

If you are looking for porn at $1.99 then you are in the wrong place. This movie does not have that. In fact, there are many things that are wrong with this film - editing, continuity, the list goes on. Compile your own list while you are watching it. But also take in the dialogue between the two actors. It feels like the director gave them a subject to explore and they did it. Quite well, I might add. But in the 72 minutes of the film the characters became more and more developed and in the end I wished that the 'breakfast' segment had been shorter and the so called 'bondage' scene (which was less bondage and more exploration) had been longer. Oh well, time for a re-make in a few years.

ACK.  What did I just watch?! LOL...  more accurately, what did I just skim through?  If you can sit through a solid 15 minutes of this crap... then you probably have two broken legs and can't reach the remote.

Don't be fooled by the premise.  It's a good one.  A woman is stuck in Alaska while her plane undergoes repairs and all the hotels get booked.  So she ends up sharing a room with another woman.  One woman has a camera on, which sits in one place on a tripod and never moves.  It's like a home video.  Half the time their heads are cut off and they are doing stupid boring crap like talking straight-girl nonsense and playing cards.  The reason one is filming at all is because she's decided being stranded in a cheap Alaskan motel with another skank is a good time to film her Master's thesis- on the fly, LOL...  does she attend Porn Hub University???  Or what?  Actually, this isn't even good enough to make the Porn Hub.

Both women are actually very pretty.  Eh... until they open their mouths.  Then you realize you're watching a very low budget soft porn flick where two straight ladies with no lez chemistry or acting ability think they're turning you on... but, of course, they are more interested in the camera (which is cutting off their heads half the time) than each other, lol.  There is a half naked massage, sleeping naked, a bath together and a silly visit to a local bondage place.  One woman even recites Shakespeare.  Boob and butt shots, if you must know.  As an MA thesis, I have to assume she never attended any classes.... FAIL.

Sheesh.  Doesn't even have comedic value for being so bad.  Don't waste your time watching this crap.  Because it's crap.  In fact, the only thing that comes to mind about this crap is... CRAP.

What started as a fun premise, turned into an amateurish film. One of the women was too matter of fact about everything, and this spoiled the film. The editing was choppy and the bondage finale literally turned me off. There is no sex between the women. Just talk.
